1. Explanation: The method log2(int x, RoundingMode mode) does not handle the case when x is 0 or negative correctly. It throws an IllegalArgumentException when x <= 0, but it does not handle the case when x is negative correctly.
   Suggested Fix: checkArgument("x", x >= 0);
2. Explanation: The method log10(int x, RoundingMode mode) does not handle the case when x is 0 or negative correctly. It throws an IllegalArgumentException when x <= 0, but it does not handle the case when x is negative correctly.
   Suggested Fix: checkArgument("x", x >= 0);
3. Explanation: The method ceilingPowerOfTwo(int x) does not handle the case when x is greater than the maximum signed power of two correctly. It throws an ArithmeticException when x > MAX_SIGNED_POWER_OF_TWO, but it does not handle the case when x is greater than the maximum signed power of two correctly.
   Suggested Fix: if (x > MAX_SIGNED_POWER_OF_TWO) { throw new ArithmeticException("ceilingPowerOfTwo(" + x + ") not representable as an int"); }
4. Explanation: The method lessThanBranchFree(int x, int y) does not handle the case when x and y are both negative correctly. It returns 1 if x < y as unsigned integers, but it does not handle the case when x and y are both negative correctly.
   Suggested Fix: if (x < 0 && y < 0) { return x > y ? 1 : 0; }

